<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-21T15:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-21T15:45:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 417.00/246</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-21T15:00:00-05:45">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I have been urged by the High Commission and many creditors who have
                                accepted awards of the Public Credit Commission to request the
                                Department to authorize as early as possible the High Commission to
                                begin payments of awards.</p>
                            <pb facs="0954" n="842" xml:id="pg_842"/>
                            <p>The High Commission cabled Nicaraguan Chargé d’Affaires Enriquez with
                                reference to this matter.</p>
                            <p>It is my opinion that payments should begin as soon as possible as it
                                will relieve the economic situation here.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>